Here is additional info on the training:

For the month of May we will be offering Team We are very excited to introduce our new
(virtual) training platform. We have been working very hard at not only continuing our training and providing the best value for our athletes and adults. But now we have stepped up our game BIG TIME with this new training app!
We will be able to host large teams virtually and create a team like atmosphere by hosting it on Zoom. We will then be able to track the data inside our training app and also monitor the athletes readiness based off (stress, sleep, mood, energy, and soreness).
Training for all sports! Summer Training will be here before we know it, and you wont have to waste a month of your summer training getting ready, if you are staying ready!
Take a look at the link below, to see the video and also the page on our website!

This is from Coach Davan at Advanteged Training.

post_text: We are looking for someone (presumably a parent, but not necessarily) to help organize the weekly spaghetti dinners that have been a Thursday tradition for the varsity football team. Basically what this person would have to do is get 3-4 parents to sign up to take care of the dinner one time and then they would be done. They would go to the school cafetorium to prepare the meal. Mike Ostermayer has already volunteered to do one dinner at his house, so we would need to cover the other 8 Thursdays for the season. The dinners have been held at the school cafetorium in the past and if we can get this going again, I will put in a request at the school to use those facilities. If you would like to p.m. if you are interested in helping out, that would be appreciated. Thank you

post_text: This is a little late in coming, but now that we have a replacement for him, I wanted to thank Kris Thompson for his time he spent as JV assistant football coach. Kris made some very positive changes to the program, and he was instrumental in redesigning our new locker room and upgrading our weightroom which were both really positive changes for everyone. Kris also brought a lot of emotion to the team and his enthusiasm will be missed this Fall (although you might still catch him on the sidelines on gameday). Thank you Kris for your effort and dedication to the team and for your continued support of the Hornets!!!!

post_text: This Sunday at 2:00 we will be having a JV and Varsity football gathering at Matt Elmblad's camp on Huron Bay. Bring your swimsuits if you like as the weather is supposed to be warm and we will be right on the lake. The directions are as follows: Take the first left past the Huron Bay Trading post on Bayview Drive. The camp will be about a half-mile down the road on the left side and I will park my red Silverado by the Elmblad sign to make it real easy to find. Please stop by and spend some time with your friends and coaches. We will be cooking hotdogs, but you don't need to bring anything unless you have something specific that you want to eat or drink. IF YOU NEED A RIDE THERE, be at the L'Anse school in front of the library at 1:30 and we will find everyone a ride.

Here are some things to think about when you are buying shoes for football. Interchangeable (detachable) cleats with turf cleats to be inserted when needed could be a good option. Now that we are playing multiple schools with the artificial turf, we need to consider different options because the cleats made for just natural grass are not effective on artificial surfaces. I will do a little more research on this and post more soon, but the following website addresses the issue that we have with playing on artificial surfaces now at Hancock, Houghton, and Calumet. I should also mention that wearing your regular athletic shoes on artificial turf can be a good option also.
http://athleteaudit.com/best-football-cleats/

post_text: Sometimes it's not whether you won or lost, but how you fought when you were down. I have never been so proud of a team as I was on Thursday night when the jv football team ran out of time against Westwood. No doubt the Patriots were a very good team, and these boys could have packed it in numerous times, but they chose to stay and fight instead. I hope that each one of these boys can take this lesson forward in their lives and realize that at this moment, when things weren't looking good for them, they got back on their feet and continued to fight like champions. On this night, these boys reminded me why football is the greatest sport in America today because they fought their fears of failure, of getting injured, of being embarrassed, and they stayed together and left it on the field. No fears, no regrets, heads held high, always!

post_text: Time is getting short to prepare for the football season. If you have goals that you still want to accomplish, and you can make it up for weightlifting at 4:00 on Monday, Wed. and Thursday (at the field), then you should seriously consider showing up for these last few weeks of lifting. Including this week, there are only 3 weeks of lifting left, and if you use this time you can still make a difference. Don't start the season with regrets. We had 12 athletes show up for the last Thursday of lifting, and 8 showed up yesterday. We also have a few going to the evening program in Baraga with Keith Denomie. These numbers are improving, but if you want it, now is the time to go get it!
